#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2021-12-02-logicdrop-automating-quarkus-with-gitlab.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The structure we settled on was to split cluster operations, templates, and "
"Quarkus services into individual projects.  This allows us to easily "
"introduce changes to existing configurations or apply new ones with minimal "
"effort and maximum flexibility."
msgstr ""
"我们确定的结构是将集群操作、模板和Quarkus服务分割成单独的项目。这使我们能够以最小的努力和最大的灵活性轻松地引入对现有配置的改变或应用新的配置。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2021-12-02-logicdrop-automating-quarkus-with-gitlab.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The *cluster* project centralizes anything touching the Kubernetes cluster. "
"It is configured as a GitLab https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/user/clusters/"
"management_project_template.html[cluster-management^] project so we can "
"manage other cluster services like Elastic, Nginx, or any other Helm charts."
msgstr ""
" *集群* 项目集中了任何触及Kubernetes集群的东西。它被配置为GitLab link:https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/"
"user/clusters/management_project_template.html[集群管理, target=\"_blank\"] "
"项目，因此我们可以管理其他集群服务，如Elastic、Nginx或任何其他Helm图表。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2021-12-02-logicdrop-automating-quarkus-with-gitlab.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The *templates* project contains the building blocks used by all our GitLab "
"projects. It makes maintenance easier, provides flexibility, and promotes "
"consistency.  Developers can add new applications or services using these "
"templates in less than a few minutes."
msgstr ""
" *模板* "
"项目包含了我们所有GitLab项目所使用的构建模块。它使维护更容易，提供灵活性，并促进一致性。开发人员可以使用这些模板在几分钟内添加新的应用程序或服务。"

#: _posts/2021-12-02-logicdrop-automating-quarkus-with-gitlab.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"*Quarkus projects* are treated as _families of services_ each worked on and "
"deployed individually. Each service uses triggers to notify the cluster when "
"it's ready to be deployed or cleaned up."
msgstr "*Quarkus 项目* 被视为 _服务家族_ ，每个服务都是单独工作和部署的。每个服务都使用触发器来通知集群何时可以部署或清理。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2021-12-02-logicdrop-automating-quarkus-with-gitlab.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"We found using https://quarkus.io/guides/config-yaml#profiles[Quarkus "
"profiles^] with abstracting common release and Kubernetes properties into a "
"shared JAR shielded developers even more from having to manage individual "
"configurations."
msgstr ""
"我们发现，使用 link:https://quarkus.io/guides/config-yaml#profiles[Quarkus配置文件, "
"target=\"_blank\"] ，将常见的发布和Kubernetes属性抽象为一个共享的JAR，使开发人员更不必管理个人配置。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2021-12-02-logicdrop-automating-quarkus-with-gitlab.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Using Quarkus we eliminated having to maintain Helm charts for the services. "
"We even have Quarkus services that interact directly with GitLab for "
"specific tooling and metrics we maintain."
msgstr ""
"使用Quarkus，我们不必再为服务维护Helm图表了。我们甚至有Quarkus服务可以直接与GitLab互动，用于我们维护的特定工具和指标。"

